'''Non-huMan''' or '''NhM''' was the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] designation for [[Alien/Legends|aliens]], [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoids]], [[Droid/Legends|droids]], [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborgs]] and [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Human/Legends|Humans]]. This label was a tool of [[High Human Culture/Legends|Human High Culture]], and it was said that NhM bigotry reached its height in the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Behind the scenes==
When composing notes on the background of his universe for licensees in [[1977]], [[George Lucas]] suggested that female [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] were not uncommon in the Empire, though few were stationed on the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]]. They were probably located in other units. As such, the bias against females in the Empire as represented in the [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] appears to have not been a part of Lucas' intent.<ref name="The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]]''</ref> However, apart from several minor references,<ref name="SW63">[[Star Wars (1977) 63|''Star Wars'' (1977) 63]]</ref><ref name="RGRCR">''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Revised Core Rulebook]]''</ref><ref name="DFSFTE">''[[Dark Forces: Soldier for the Empire]]''</ref> few female stormtroopers were referred to or appeared in licensed materials or the movies until the ''[[Star Wars: Legacy]]'' comic series.<ref name="Star Wars: Legacy 2006 0">[[Star Wars: Legacy (2006) 0|''Star Wars: Legacy'' (2006) 0]]</ref><ref name="Legacy 2006 4">[[Legacy (2006) 4|''Legacy'' (2006) 4]]</ref>

